{
  "texts": [
    "This gives 3,853/500/948 samples for train/dev/test respectively.",
    "We randomly sample 4,000 instances from the original train split of QAMPARI and take its entire development and test splits, giving 4,000/1,000/1,000 samples for train/dev/test usage.",
    "ELI5The original ELI5 dataset is much larger than ASQA.",
    "To ensure the balance between different datasets, we randomly sample 3,728/1,000/1,000 instances from the train/dev/test splits of ELI5.",
    "We also include in the train split 264 samples from WebGPT (Nakano et al., 2021), since these samples' answers contain citations and are of relatively high quality."
  ]
